         <mod eID="c58-0033__main__d6e2652"/>ute this <lb n="c58-0033__main__3"/> dear revenge will I again behold the sun and <lb n="c58-0033__main__4"/> tread the green herbage of earth which otherwise <lb n="c58-0033__main__5"/> should vanish from my eyes for ever. And I call <lb n="c58-0033__main__6"/> on you, spirits of the dead; and on you, wandering <lb n="c58-0033__main__7"/> ministers of vengeance, to aid and conduct me in <lb n="c58-0033__main__8"/> my work. Let the cursed and hellish monster drink <lb n="c58-0033__main__9"/> deep of agony; let him feel the despair that now <lb n="c58-0033__main__10"/> torments me!<milestone xmlns:mith="http://mith.umd.edu/sc/ns1#" unit="tei:p"/> 
         <lb n="c58-0033__main__11"/> I had begun my adjuration with solemnity, <lb n="c58-0033__main__12"/> and an awe that almost assured me that the shades <lb n="c58-0033__main__13"/> of my murdered friends heard and approved my devotion. <lb n="c58-0033__main__14"/> But <mod sID="c58-0033__main__d6e2693"/>
            <del rend="strikethrough" sID="c58-0033__main__d6e2695"/>rage<del eID="c58-0033__main__d6e2695"/>
