         <add eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2811"/>Amidst the wilds of Tartary and Russia although <lb n="c58-0035__main__7"/> he still evaded me I <del rend="strikethrough" sID="c58-0035__main__d6e2819"/>e<del eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2819"/> have ever followed in his <lb n="c58-0035__main__8"/> tract. Sometimes the peasants <add place="intralinear" sID="c58-0035__main__d6e2825"/>s<add eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2825"/>cared by <add place="intralinear" sID="c58-0035__main__d6e2828"/>t<add eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2828"/>his horrid <lb n="c58-0035__main__9"/> appar<add place="intralinear" sID="c58-0035__main__d6e2833"/>i<add eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2833"/>tion informed me of his path; sometimes <lb n="c58-0035__main__10"/> he himself, who feared that if I lost all trace I should <lb n="c58-0035__main__11"/> despair and die, often left some mark to guide <lb n="c58-0035__main__12"/> me. The snows descended on my head and I saw the prin<add place="intralinear" sID="c58-0035__main__d6e2843"/>t<add eID="c58-0035__main__d6e2843"/> 
